    application:
      "When grief over loss or injustice feels too large for polite prayer, let this psalm's raw honesty give you permission to lament specifically and urgently rather than softening your words to God. Notice that the psalmist's ultimate appeal is to God's own name and glory, not merely his own relief—consider praying that way when your own situation feels unresolved. Practice ending hard prayers, as this psalm does, with a forward-looking vow of praise rather than only present complaint.",
